00:48:45,189 --> 00:48:46,157
Jude!

519
00:48:47,158 --> 00:48:48,224
Come on, buddy!

520
00:48:48,226 --> 00:48:49,728
It's not funny, Jude!

521
00:48:52,330 --> 00:48:53,497
I'll go this way.

522
00:48:53,499 --> 00:48:56,165
- You head off that way.
- Okay.

523
00:48:56,167 --> 00:48:57,503
We'll circle round.
We'll meet back at the house.

524
00:48:58,504 --> 00:48:59,638
Jude!

525
00:49:00,673 --> 00:49:02,171
Jude!

526
00:49:02,173 --> 00:49:03,374
Jude!

527
00:50:14,078 --> 00:50:15,113
Jude?

528
00:50:41,239 --> 00:50:42,240
Jude?

529
00:50:45,143 --> 00:50:46,678
Jude.

530
00:50:55,788 --> 00:50:56,755
Jude?

531
00:51:00,958 --> 00:51:03,827
Jude? Is that you?

532
00:51:03,829 --> 00:51:05,363
Jude, what are you doing?

533
00:51:11,369 --> 00:51:13,971
Jude, where are you?

534
00:51:25,684 --> 00:51:26,951
Look, Mommy.

535
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:29,888
Over here.

536
00:51:32,223 --> 00:51:34,025
Come play with us, Mommy.

537
00:52:34,386 --> 00:52:35,587
Jude?

538
00:53:33,812 --> 00:53:34,780
Jude.

539
00:53:43,488 --> 00:53:45,254
I'm sorry I scared you.

540
00:53:45,256 --> 00:53:48,324
- We were just playing, Mommy.
- It's so good to hear your voice.

541
00:53:59,638 --> 00:54:01,471
There you are.

542
00:54:01,473 --> 00:54:03,274
Been looking all over for you.
Didn't you hear us calling?

543
00:54:03,875 --> 00:54:05,942
No.

544
00:54:05,944 --> 00:54:08,378
Jude. What the hell are
you doing in here? It's not safe.

545
00:54:08,380 --> 00:54:09,313
I'm sorry, Daddy.

546
00:54:10,549 --> 00:54:11,817
Jude, he's...

547
00:54:13,018 --> 00:54:14,316
You're talking.

548
00:54:14,318 --> 00:54:15,885
Right, let's go.

549
00:54:15,887 --> 00:54:17,687
We're not really supposed to
be in this part of the house.

550
00:54:17,689 --> 00:54:18,557
Come on.

551
00:54:23,028 --> 00:54:25,030
It's so nice
to hear you talking.

552
00:54:35,373 --> 00:54:37,409
Joseph,
what happened in this house?

553
00:54:39,243 --> 00:54:42,179
Jude, why don't you go
show Brahms the music room?

554
00:54:43,081 --> 00:54:44,016
Stay close, mate.

555
00:54:45,851 --> 00:54:46,752
There, uh...

556
00:54:48,420 --> 00:54:52,254
There was a family that
lived here a long time ago.

557
00:54:52,256 --> 00:54:54,424
Had a son, went a bit mad.

558
00:54:54,426 --> 00:54:56,026
Killed a little girl.

559
00:54:56,028 --> 00:54:59,429
Got burnt up in fire.
Wore a mask to hide it.

560
00:54:59,431 --> 00:55:01,731
Lived inside the walls
of the house for 30 years.

561
00:55:01,733 --> 00:55:03,232
Never came out.

562
00:55:03,234 --> 00:55:04,403
The Heelshires?

563
00:55:05,037 --> 00:55:06,438
Yeah, the Heelshires.

564
00:55:08,040 --> 00:55:09,007
And?

565
00:55:10,509 --> 00:55:13,009
And the parents
committed suicide.

566
00:55:13,011 --> 00:55:14,077
Drowned themselves.

567
00:55:14,079 --> 00:55:15,747
It's a very sad story.

568
00:55:16,615 --> 00:55:18,448
And the son?

569
00:55:18,450 --> 00:55:22,052
Well, it all got a bit
messy after the parents had gone.

570
00:55:22,054 --> 00:55:25,287
He killed a man,
very nearly two others,

571
00:55:25,289 --> 00:55:27,392
before he was killed himself.

572
00:55:28,794 --> 00:55:30,595
But they're all dead
and buried now.

573
00:55:33,364 --> 00:55:34,933
What's the son's name?

574
00:55:36,802 --> 00:55:38,937
His name was Brahms.

575
00:55:40,539 --> 00:55:42,439
Did you say Brahms?

576
00:55:42,441 --> 00:55:44,306
I'm sorry.
I didn't mean to keep it from you.

577
00:55:44,308 --> 00:55:46,945
I just didn't think
it'd ever come up.

578
00:55:47,646 --> 00:55:49,548
Thank you for telling us.

579
00:55:52,617 --> 00:55:54,152
Come on, Jude.
It's time to go home.

580
00:55:59,256 --> 00:56:00,257
Hey, Joseph?

581
00:56:01,460 --> 00:56:02,761
Did you ever find your dog?

582
00:56:03,829 --> 00:56:05,161
Yes, I did.

583
00:56:05,163 --> 00:56:07,432
I'm afraid Oz was found
gutted in the forest.

584
00:56:11,903 --> 00:56:13,138
I'm sorry to hear that.

585
00:56:18,110 --> 00:56:20,612
<i>So, your parents tell me
you've been talking again.</i>

586
00:56:23,247 --> 00:56:25,749
<i>Is this your new friend
Brahms?</i>

587
00:56:25,751 --> 00:56:28,019
<i>He seems like
a very nice friend.</i>

588
00:56:29,821 --> 00:56:32,122
<i>What are some of the things
you talk about?</i>

589
00:56:32,124 --> 00:56:35,925
He... tells me
all sorts of things.

590
00:56:35,927 --> 00:56:39,361
Sometimes he tells me about the
other families he's lived with.

591
00:56:39,363 --> 00:56:41,967
<i>Oh. Has he lived
with a lot of families?</i>

592
00:56:43,435 --> 00:56:46,268
He wants to live
with us now.

593
00:56:46,270 --> 00:56:49,439
He was very angry that Mommy and
Daddy wanted to take him away.

594
00:56:49,441 --> 00:56:50,640
<i>Oh.</i>

595
00:56:50,642 --> 00:56:52,142
<i>And when Brahms gets angry,</i>

596
00:56:52,144 --> 00:56:55,781
<i>does he say he wants to
hurt someone or something?</i>

597
00:56:59,384 --> 00:57:02,988
<i>Is there something he wants
to tell your mum and dad?</i>

598
00:57:07,058 --> 00:57:10,126
<i>Well, if Jude had something
to do with the dog's death,</i>

599
00:57:10,128 --> 00:57:13,362
<i>then this is a lot more
serious than we thought.</i>

600
00:57:13,364 --> 00:57:16,032
<i>The doll might be enabling him
to shift blame</i>

601
00:57:16,034 --> 00:57:18,201
<i>for all the bad things
that he might do.</i>

602
00:57:18,203 --> 00:57:22,639
<i>I think it would be a good idea
for me to see him face-to-face.</i>

603
00:57:22,641 --> 00:57:25,074
<i>When do you think you can
bring him down to London?</i>

604
00:57:25,076 --> 00:57:27,844
We've got guests coming today,
but we'll bring him as soon as we can.

605
00:57:27,846 --> 00:57:29,712
<i>All right, then.</i>

606
00:57:29,714 --> 00:57:32,316
<i>But I urge you,
keep a close eye on him in the meanwhile.</i>

607
00:58:02,414 --> 00:58:04,346
Jude! Everyone's here.

608
00:58:04,348 --> 00:58:06,348
- Anything goes. Make yourself at home.
- Thank you.

609
00:58:06,350 --> 00:58:09,052
This is just fabulous!
I love it.

610
00:58:09,054 --> 00:58:10,555
Hello.

611
00:58:14,292 --> 00:58:16,759
Well, look. There he is.

612
00:58:16,761 --> 00:58:19,629
You remember your old Uncle
Liam, don't you?

613
00:58:19,631 --> 00:58:21,731
- Hey.
- What? It's not my fault he's mental.

614
00:58:21,733 --> 00:58:22,934
Shh, shh, shh.

615
00:58:24,202 --> 00:58:28,370
And...
who's this handsome chap?

616
00:58:28,372 --> 00:58:30,540
Brahms.

617
00:58:30,542 --> 00:58:33,376
Well. Hello there, Brahms.
Pleased to meet you.

618
00:58:33,378 --> 00:58:35,914
Any friend of Jude's
is a friend of mine.

619
00:58:37,816 --> 00:58:39,816
Okay, children,
why don't we go outside and play

620
00:58:39,818 --> 00:58:41,718
while we all have a catch-up.

621
00:58:41,720 --> 00:58:42,919
Yes.

622
00:58:42,921 --> 00:58:44,988
There's nothing to do outside.

623
00:58:44,990 --> 00:58:46,623
There's nature. All right?

624
00:58:46,625 --> 00:58:49,292
It's like a video game,
but real. Go, enjoy.

625
00:58:49,294 --> 00:58:50,795
Come on, Jude.
Show them around.

626
00:58:53,565 --> 00:58:56,099
- Maybe I should go with them.
- Nonsense. They'll be fine.

627
00:58:56,101 --> 00:58:57,736
Just stay close
to the house, guys.

628
00:58:59,404 --> 00:59:01,439
- This is so cool.
- Shut up.

629
00:59:05,677 --> 00:59:06,910
I like your doll.

630
00:59:06,912 --> 00:59:07,812
Thanks.

631
00:59:11,416 --> 00:59:14,918
This place sucks.
There's nothing to do here.

632
00:59:14,920 --> 00:59:16,419
We could play croquet.

633
00:59:16,421 --> 00:59:17,987
I wanna play.
Come on.

634
00:59:17,989 --> 00:59:19,858
Don't touch him, Sophie.
He's mental.

635
00:59:21,259 --> 00:59:22,959
No, I'm not.

636
00:59:22,961 --> 00:59:26,296
My parents say you talk to that
doll, like it's a real person.

637
00:59:26,298 --> 00:59:29,432
Because you went crazy
when your mum got attacked.

638
00:59:29,434 --> 00:59:31,634
And we're not supposed
to notice.

639
00:59:31,636 --> 00:59:32,835
Will!

640
00:59:32,837 --> 00:59:36,205
But they know you're mental.

641
00:59:36,207 --> 00:59:39,042
And I know you're mental.

642
00:59:39,044 --> 00:59:41,044
And your stupid doll,

643
00:59:41,046 --> 00:59:42,347
he's the most mental of all.

644
00:59:51,356 --> 00:59:53,024
He's fine, Liza.

645
00:59:54,559 --> 00:59:55,894
Have some wine.

646
00:59:58,496 --> 01:00:01,130
It'll do him good to hang out
with some other children.

647
01:00:01,132 --> 01:00:02,067
Yeah.

648
01:00:04,970 --> 01:00:06,037
I'm sorry.

649
01:00:09,574 --> 01:00:11,309
Ever since it happened,
I just...

650
01:00:13,511 --> 01:00:16,312
I can't seem to relax.

651
01:00:16,314 --> 01:00:18,214
Hey, you're with family now.

652
01:00:18,216 --> 01:00:20,018
You don't have anything
to worry about.

653
01:00:21,853 --> 01:00:23,389
And Will won't let
anything happen.

654
01:00:26,392 --> 01:00:27,690
Hey, you're breaking it!

655
01:00:27,692 --> 01:00:30,727
- Shut up, nutter.
- Stop it, Will!

656
01:00:30,729 --> 01:00:33,598
Oh, you're sticking up
for your nutter boyfriend now.

657
01:00:37,669 --> 01:00:40,169
Maybe I should
just smash your doll.

658
01:00:40,171 --> 01:00:42,839
- Maybe that will make you normal again.
- Don't.

659
01:00:42,841 --> 01:00:44,907
We get to this party,

660
01:00:44,909 --> 01:00:46,776
and we have literally
just walked in the door,

661
01:00:46,778 --> 01:00:50,046
and his pants split
right in the bum.

662
01:00:50,048 --> 01:00:53,049
And not just a little tear,
the whole bum!

663
01:00:53,051 --> 01:00:54,617
I'm going to tell Mum!

664
01:00:54,619 --> 01:00:56,054
She'll probably be happy.

665
01:00:56,955 --> 01:00:58,554
Don't touch him.

666
01:00:58,556 --> 01:01:00,223
Or what?

667
01:01:00,225 --> 01:01:03,094
Or he'll make you wish
you never came here.

668
01:01:04,229 --> 01:01:05,595
Did you buy him purple boxers?

669
01:01:05,597 --> 01:01:07,431
I did.

670
01:01:07,433 --> 01:01:08,698
Kinky.

671
01:01:08,700 --> 01:01:11,435
It's good to see
that smile again, Liza.

672
01:01:11,437 --> 01:01:12,471
That old smile of yours.

673
01:01:15,240 --> 01:01:17,540
- Give it back!
- Nah, I don't think I will.

674
01:01:17,542 --> 01:01:19,108
Give it back to her.

675
01:01:19,110 --> 01:01:21,911
Ooh, now your boyfriend's mad.

676
01:01:21,913 --> 01:01:23,913
Why don't you come get it
from me, mental?

677
01:01:23,915 --> 01:01:26,450
I wouldn't worry
about this doll thing.

678
01:01:26,452 --> 01:01:28,651
Will used to be obsessed
with this blanket.

679
01:01:28,653 --> 01:01:29,986
Run, mental, run.

680
01:01:29,988 --> 01:01:31,222
Stop it, Will!

681
01:01:32,090 --> 01:01:34,157
Obsessed.

682
01:01:34,159 --> 01:01:38,561
Then one day I realized that it was
quite literally a security blanket.

683
01:01:38,563 --> 01:01:40,630
I think this doll
could be the same thing.

684
01:01:40,632 --> 01:01:42,265
Come on, mental.

685
01:01:42,267 --> 01:01:44,734
You shouldn't worry about it,
is what I'm saying.

686
01:01:44,736 --> 01:01:47,070
Kids do all sorts
of weird things.

687
01:01:47,072 --> 01:01:49,072
They go through phases.

688
01:01:49,074 --> 01:01:50,474
And then poof, it's gone.

689
01:02:20,872 --> 01:02:23,608
- Oh, my God.
- What? What's going on?

690
01:02:24,142 --> 01:02:25,343
Will!

691
01:02:29,147 --> 01:02:30,547
Easy, on three. One, two, three.

692
01:02:30,549 --> 01:02:31,714
Mind his head!

693
01:02:31,716 --> 01:02:33,349
Slowly. Slowly.

694
01:02:33,351 --> 01:02:35,120
Mary, help
with his head, okay?

695
01:02:36,688 --> 01:02:38,855
Will, I'm coming in.

696
01:02:38,857 --> 01:02:40,291
Sophie, get in the front.

697
01:03:08,554 --> 01:03:10,753
Sweetheart, why don't you
drink some of this?

698
01:03:10,755 --> 01:03:12,054
It'll help you sleep.

699
01:03:12,056 --> 01:03:13,658
A nap will do you good.

700
01:03:19,330 --> 01:03:20,231
Okay?

701
01:03:26,204 --> 01:03:27,071
There you go.

702
01:03:31,577 --> 01:03:32,611
Mommy.

703
01:03:40,051 --> 01:03:41,853
Everything's okay.

704
01:03:46,357 --> 01:03:48,291
He won't let me go.

705
01:03:48,293 --> 01:03:51,961
He wants me to live in the
big house with him forever.

706
01:03:51,963 --> 01:03:55,800
He said he'd kill you and
Daddy if I didn't do it.

707
01:03:57,902 --> 01:03:58,903
He said that?

708
01:04:03,775 --> 01:04:05,043
When did he say that?

709
01:04:06,978 --> 01:04:08,880
He says it all the time.

710
01:04:10,215 --> 01:04:12,616
I can't control him
anymore.

711
01:04:12,618 --> 01:04:14,653
He keeps getting stronger.

712
01:04:16,221 --> 01:04:17,720
Well,

713
01:04:17,722 --> 01:04:19,625
no one's gonna hurt
Mommy and Daddy.

714
01:04:21,125 --> 01:04:22,327
And no one's gonna hurt you.

715
01:04:23,429 --> 01:04:24,396
Okay?

716
01:05:20,686 --> 01:05:22,151
Hey, Liza, it's me.

717
01:05:22,153 --> 01:05:24,887
We just saw the doctor.
I think Will's gonna be okay.

718
01:05:24,889 --> 01:05:27,056
So, I'll call you
from the car.

719
01:05:27,058 --> 01:05:28,226
All right.
I love you. Bye.

720
01:06:00,392 --> 01:06:02,392
Not from around here,
are you?

721
01:06:02,394 --> 01:06:03,893
I'm staying
at the Glennview Estates.

722
01:06:03,895 --> 01:06:05,229
Glennview?

723
01:06:06,331 --> 01:06:09,499
Oh, you mean the Heelshire place.

724
01:06:09,501 --> 01:06:12,103
Christ, you couldn't pay me
money to stop there.

725
01:06:13,171 --> 01:06:14,740
- You what?
- You don't know?

726
01:06:16,742 --> 01:06:19,710
Whole family went
completely mad out there.

727
01:06:19,712 --> 01:06:23,014
Something to do with a son living
inside the walls for years.

728
01:06:34,760 --> 01:06:38,127
You see, but that's not the only
thing that happened out there.

729
01:06:38,129 --> 01:06:41,864
There were other
tragedies before.

730
01:06:41,866 --> 01:06:47,303
Back in the '50s, a kid killed
his own mother and brother,

731
01:06:47,305 --> 01:06:49,575
convinced a doll
was speaking to him.

732
01:06:57,383 --> 01:06:59,215
And it's still going on.

733
01:06:59,217 --> 01:07:03,886
Last year, that city man that
bought it after the Heelshires

734
01:07:03,888 --> 01:07:06,322
went a bit mad
and disappeared.

735
01:07:06,324 --> 01:07:08,324
Never heard from again.

736
01:07:08,326 --> 01:07:10,761
I saw him down the pub
one time.

737
01:07:10,763 --> 01:07:12,895
Old crazy Joe.

738
01:07:12,897 --> 01:07:14,230
Crazy Joe?

739
01:07:14,232 --> 01:07:15,931
That's what people
called him, mind.

740
01:07:15,933 --> 01:07:16,835
His name were Joseph...

741
01:07:54,473 --> 01:07:56,305
Oh, my God. Jude!

742
01:07:56,307 --> 01:07:57,275
Jude!

743
01:07:57,810 --> 01:07:58,710
Jude!

744
01:08:02,313 --> 01:08:03,181
Jude!

745
01:08:07,719 --> 01:08:09,353
Didn't have to be like this.

746
01:08:13,157 --> 01:08:14,058
Joseph.

747
01:08:15,527 --> 01:08:16,728
Is Jude okay?

748
01:08:18,397 --> 01:08:20,499
Don't worry. He's safe.

749
01:08:22,835 --> 01:08:25,404
Safer now than he's probably
ever been in his life.

750
01:08:26,204 --> 01:08:27,138
Why are you here?

751
01:08:29,006 --> 01:08:31,175
I'm here because
he wants me to be.

752
01:08:32,176 --> 01:08:33,044
Who?

753
01:08:34,178 --> 01:08:35,346
Brahms.

754
01:08:38,417 --> 01:08:41,918
He doesn't like it like this,
but you've done it to yourself.

755
01:08:41,920 --> 01:08:43,352
I just wanna know
where my son is.

756
01:08:43,354 --> 01:08:45,187
I will do anything you want.
Just give me my son.

757
01:08:45,189 --> 01:08:47,089
I want you to listen!

758
01:08:47,091 --> 01:08:49,495
He wants you to listen!

759
01:08:51,663 --> 01:08:53,998
You asked me why I'm here.

760
01:08:54,867 --> 01:08:56,535
It's the same reason
that you are.

761
01:08:57,603 --> 01:08:59,368
He called me.

762
01:08:59,370 --> 01:09:01,507
He calls out to the ones
that need him.

763
01:09:02,774 --> 01:09:04,374
The damaged ones.

764
01:09:04,376 --> 01:09:06,244
He looks inside you.

765
01:09:08,079 --> 01:09:09,180
It was just a whisper...

766
01:09:10,516 --> 01:09:11,850
at first,

767
01:09:12,918 --> 01:09:14,520
when I first came here.

768
01:09:15,119 --> 01:09:16,220
So quiet.

769
01:09:17,723 --> 01:09:19,923
And he was in pieces
when I found him,

770
01:09:19,925 --> 01:09:21,292
broken.

771
01:09:23,462 --> 01:09:24,796
And then the voice said...

772
01:09:25,531 --> 01:09:27,031
to put him back together.

773
01:09:29,635 --> 01:09:30,936
So I did.

774
01:09:36,808 --> 01:09:39,308
Then I heard him,
growing inside.

775
01:09:39,310 --> 01:09:40,144
You must've heard it.

776
01:09:42,481 --> 01:09:44,783
Jude sure has. Oh, yeah.

