01:09:45,484 --> 01:09:47,617
I don't know what Brahms is,

778
01:09:47,619 --> 01:09:50,087
but you can stop this.

779
01:09:50,789 --> 01:09:52,455
It's too late.

780
01:09:52,457 --> 01:09:56,225
Brahms and Jude are gonna be
one, and it'll be beautiful.

781
01:09:56,227 --> 01:09:58,397
Everybody thought
that I was crazy.

782
01:09:59,998 --> 01:10:01,733
They thought the Heelshires were
crazy, but, oh, no.

783
01:10:03,167 --> 01:10:05,003
It's always been the doll.

784
01:10:08,907 --> 01:10:11,841
Even before the house, before the
Davies, the ones before that.

785
01:10:11,843 --> 01:10:13,108
I found all their old letters.

786
01:10:13,110 --> 01:10:16,415
He knew that you were coming.

787
01:10:18,016 --> 01:10:20,819
He knew your boy
would find him.

788
01:10:22,353 --> 01:10:24,754
That's why he told me
to bury him.

789
01:10:24,756 --> 01:10:27,124
They're always so curious, aren't they?
The little ones are like...

790
01:10:29,093 --> 01:10:30,493
like moths to a flame.

791
01:10:30,495 --> 01:10:33,130
Joseph, where is my son?

792
01:10:33,699 --> 01:10:35,599
I wanna see my son!

793
01:10:35,601 --> 01:10:38,336
He's in the big house!

794
01:10:50,314 --> 01:10:51,282
Jude!

795
01:10:56,021 --> 01:10:56,989
Jude!

796
01:11:00,492 --> 01:11:01,460
Jude!

797
01:11:23,347 --> 01:11:24,583
Jude.

798
01:11:26,818 --> 01:11:28,652
Jude?

799
01:11:28,654 --> 01:11:30,154
<i>Over here.</i>

800
01:11:48,874 --> 01:11:50,509
<i>This way.</i>

801
01:12:09,293 --> 01:12:10,462
<i>We're just over here.</i>

802
01:12:47,132 --> 01:12:48,133
Jude...

803
01:12:58,910 --> 01:13:01,012
I know you don't
wanna hurt anybody.

804
01:13:03,415 --> 01:13:05,117
This isn't you, Jude.

805
01:13:08,687 --> 01:13:10,756
Please, put him down.

806
01:13:12,758 --> 01:13:14,358
It's going to be okay.

807
01:13:17,361 --> 01:13:18,597
Can I hold Brahms?

808
01:13:35,881 --> 01:13:37,983
I used to hold you
just like this.

809
01:13:43,054 --> 01:13:44,623
Let's just put him down.

810
01:13:56,535 --> 01:13:57,836
Hello, Mommy.

811
01:14:01,573 --> 01:14:03,742
Jude, put the gun down.

812
01:14:05,911 --> 01:14:07,412
We're very angry.

813
01:14:08,847 --> 01:14:10,715
You and Daddy
have been getting in the way.

814
01:14:13,251 --> 01:14:15,352
We're going to
live here now...

815
01:14:17,088 --> 01:14:18,423
because you can't protect us.

816
01:14:20,192 --> 01:14:21,526
Protect you from who?

817
01:14:22,427 --> 01:14:23,360
That dog.

818
01:14:25,063 --> 01:14:25,897
Will.

819
01:14:27,732 --> 01:14:30,168
And those men from that night.

820
01:14:32,204 --> 01:14:33,271
You're right.

821
01:14:34,873 --> 01:14:37,442
- We do need Brahms to protect us.
- It's too late.

822
01:14:38,176 --> 01:14:40,111
You've given us no choice.

823
01:14:40,912 --> 01:14:42,745
Goodbye, Mommy.

824
01:14:42,747 --> 01:14:47,252
I know Brahms
is telling you what to say.

825
01:14:49,554 --> 01:14:52,889
Which is why we need to
take him home with us.

826
01:14:52,891 --> 01:14:55,393
Brahms needs to be
a member of our family.

827
01:14:57,229 --> 01:14:59,931
And what kind of a family
doesn't need a mother?

828
01:15:18,049 --> 01:15:19,217
Mom?

829
01:15:27,392 --> 01:15:28,426
Jude.

830
01:15:30,962 --> 01:15:31,830
What have you done?

831
01:15:34,132 --> 01:15:35,100
What have you done?

832
01:15:36,268 --> 01:15:37,168
Stay back.

833
01:15:39,504 --> 01:15:42,672
It's me he'll punish.
I'm the one who didn't protect him.

834
01:15:42,674 --> 01:15:43,907
No, no.

835
01:15:43,909 --> 01:15:45,911
Joseph, Brahms can't
hurt you anymore.

836
01:15:47,178 --> 01:15:48,280
You don't understand.

837
01:15:48,914 --> 01:15:50,415
It will never be over.

838
01:17:15,600 --> 01:17:17,403
It's gonna be
all right, Brahms.

839
01:18:08,887 --> 01:18:10,487
Mom! You're home.

840
01:18:10,489 --> 01:18:12,155
Yes. I missed you.

841
01:18:12,157 --> 01:18:13,890
- I missed you too.
- Really?

842
01:18:13,892 --> 01:18:15,758
- Perfect timing.
- Hey.

843
01:18:15,760 --> 01:18:17,126
Hey, beautiful.
How was your day?

844
01:18:17,128 --> 01:18:18,761
It was good.

845
01:18:18,763 --> 01:18:21,631
I think we might sign that
author I was telling you about.

846
01:18:21,633 --> 01:18:23,266
Yeah? Nice!

847
01:18:23,268 --> 01:18:24,501
All righty.

848
01:18:24,503 --> 01:18:26,437
- This looks so good.
- Thank you.

849
01:18:26,439 --> 01:18:28,671
Wait until you taste it,
because I'm pretty confident

850
01:18:28,673 --> 01:18:32,608
that this might be the greatest coq
au vin ever made upon English shores.

851
01:18:32,610 --> 01:18:34,343
I'm not even joking.

852
01:18:34,345 --> 01:18:36,447
There's a whole bottle of wine in
here, so I'm not sure if...

853
01:18:36,449 --> 01:18:38,081
No, okay.
I will give you some.

854
01:18:38,083 --> 01:18:39,849
- Thank you.
- All right.

855
01:18:39,851 --> 01:18:41,150
This looks so good.

856
01:18:41,152 --> 01:18:42,585
Thank you.

857
01:18:42,587 --> 01:18:44,787
Just two or three hours
of my day. Nothing much.

858
01:18:46,357 --> 01:18:47,824
Is it my turn tomorrow?

859
01:18:47,826 --> 01:18:49,360
Yeah. Cheers.

860
01:18:50,628 --> 01:18:52,263
Good night, my man.
You sleep tight.

861
01:18:54,099 --> 01:18:55,698
I love you, sweetie.

862
01:18:55,700 --> 01:18:56,935
Love you too.

863
01:19:01,440 --> 01:19:02,340
Good night.

864
01:19:59,831 --> 01:20:01,099
Good night, Brahms.

865
01:20:02,601 --> 01:20:04,503
I think we'll be happy here.

866
01:20:06,070 --> 01:20:07,772
If they learn the rules.

